{
  "stem": "6258.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You call this life?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was very unreal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at the beginning, I think that we all felt-- at least I felt-- it is something like, let's say, temporarily, vacation, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother had a wonderful saying.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She always said, 'Nothing takes such a long time as temporally, or in the meantime.' And in the meantime, one has to live.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we really-- the Germans said that they are making ghetto in order to save us from the anti-Semitic Poles.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What was, of course, ridiculous.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then-- so not knowing Yiddish, and not knowing Hebrew, when we were working with my mother and some other people too who were also not-- well, like-- like we-- on the streets, we could not even read the signs on the stores, because they were all supposed to be in Hebrew or in Yiddish, and not in Polish.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyway, during the first two or three months, it was not so bad.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It could be worse, we thought.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There-- but later on, when the walls were fixed, and it was not allowed to go out without special permission-- and who got special permission?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Almost no one.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So therefore, it was very difficult, and nobody knew how to organize our life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then this is when people, themselves, say, someone has to take care of the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Someone had to take care of the hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At this time, my brother was already home, and he was working in the Jewish hospital.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Having already been trained?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was-- as-- well, how do you call?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like a trained nurse or assistant to a, by the way, very famous surgeon, Dr.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nussenfeld.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well-- so he was working there.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
